Elon Musk is a business magnate, industrial designer, and engineer. He is the CEO, CTO, and co-founder of SpaceX; CEO, Product Architect of Tesla, Inc.; founder of Neuralink and The Boring Company; and co-founder of PayPal. Born on June 28, 1971, in Pretoria, South Africa, Musk moved to the United States when he was 17 to attend the University of Pennsylvania. His innovative businesses and forward-thinking ideas have made significant impacts in various industries such as space travel, renewable energy, electric cars, and more.

Musk's accomplishments have had a significant impact on technology and science.

Elon Musk has six children in total. His first five children were born from two previous marriages:

1. Ivan Musk (born 1995) - Son with Justine Wilson, his first wife.
2. Griffin Musk (born 2004) and Xavier Musk (born 2006) - Sons with his second wife, Talulah Rowe.
3. Kai and Saxon Musk (born 2009 and 2010 respectively) - Sons with his third wife, Clare Elise Musk.

In addition to these, Elon Musk also had a child, named X Æ A-Xii, born in 2020 with his current partner, Grimes.
